      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p /><p /><p /><p>Adding edge breakup to props is a common practice, often achieved by painting masks in texturing software like Adobe Painter or The Foundry’s Mari.  </p><p>At Pixar, however, we tend to take a procedural approach to edge breakup.  </p><p>This allows retaining creative control, such as quickly reacting to the director's notes without repainting and exporting edge masks, and creating shading variants on props, from a new-looking prop to various stages of wear and damage.</p><p>Below is a quick guide to procedural edge masks.</p><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"2d27b9c0-1712-469d-90d4-4728edae363d\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">Step One</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>Let’s start by adding a PxrCurvature node with the default settings to our geometry.  In this example, we’re going to use the RenderMan University shield.  </p><p>As you can see from the first render, it’s not very impressive … but worry not, in a few simple steps we’ll vastly improve the look.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760093489425&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760093489425&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623509665\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"a02db951-19fc-4566-9151-76e1fdb8338f\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760093489425&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760093489425&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"81ad2bb6-9376-4f86-80ad-315fdc501070\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">Step Two</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>The next step is to adjust some of the default settings.</p><p>The first thing we want to do is make the curvature brighter, so increasing the Output Gain from 1 to 10 immediately produces a stronger signal.  </p><p>Increasing the number of samples from 4 to 8 (or 16) will reduce some of the grain in the curvature, but will slightly increase the render time.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760094144015&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760094144015&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623640714\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"9dac6a72-bc59-4274-bc8a-246b2f68ee4a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760094144015&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760094144015&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><p /><p>Next, we'll load a map to start breaking up the curvature.  In this example, I’ve used grunge_04.tex from our Grunge Texture Vol 1 Pack, and mapped using a PxrRoundCube+PxrMultiTexture (Triplanar) approach.</p><p>To add a bit more contrast to the grunge map, a PxrThreshold node is used to achieve this effect.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095032391&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095032391&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623575281\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"c34d6be3-a181-4339-8f09-f7299a45d853\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095032391&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095032391&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><p /><p>Using a PxrBlend node, we can subtract the grunge map from the curvature by setting the mode to Subtract.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095239060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095239060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623542499\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"0cd9e3c5-8c58-493b-8fb7-9a19f0fb52e3\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095239060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095239060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"6a1d7a1b-3ba5-4d92-9248-c2f0d3cf1dc2\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">Step Three</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>Now we’re starting to get somewhere useful for use as a mask between two layers or to add bump/displacement to the edges of the shield.</p><p>The last step in this simple example is to increase the brightness of our result, and here we’re using a PxrSplineMap node. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095647229&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095647229&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623640727\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"8239d83c-ec11-49e0-a8ee-4b5037daa5a9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095647229&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095647229&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095993423&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=374\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095993423&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"748\" data-width=\"1517\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623542508\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"d59fe5a9-005a-4e1a-adb3-2cc482053f3f\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095993423&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1517&amp;height=748 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760095993423&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=374 1x\"></span><p /><p>Great, now we have a mask that’s more useful for our purposes, but it’s worth noting that this example is just a straightforward approach.  </p><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"f5eeeef4-8956-40fa-aea3-53c37fb8d7e9\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #4C9AFF;\">\n<p><strong><span class=\"legacy-color-text-inverse\">Refine Details</span></strong></p>\n</div></div><p>To increase the realism, you could try subtracting the curvature with multiple grunge maps, adding more detail, and breaking up your mask.</p><p>Below is an example where two grunge maps are layered over the curvature, using a PxrLayeredBlend node to handle the blending modes of the layered maps.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096865953&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096865953&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"714\" data-width=\"1695\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623509685\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"e4619d20-303e-4c52-a12e-ca8f61c48717\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096865953&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=640 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_6.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096865953&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=320 1x\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096883039&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=538\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096883039&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1075\" data-width=\"1517\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"623542516\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"502759691\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"5\" data-media-id=\"a39e65d7-b7fa-45f7-9a35-c3c5845348c2\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096883039&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1517&amp;height=1075 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/502759691/ProceduralEdgeBreak_nodes2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1760096883039&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=538 1x\"></span><p /><p /><p />"
